title: All The EMOTIONAL Moments Of The 2020 Golden Globe Awards!
tags: Clevver|clevver news|hearst|news feed|celebrity news|celeb news|entertainment news|golden globes|golden globe awards|golden globes 2019|golden globes 2020|ellen degeneres|charlize theron|jennifer aniston|kate mckinnon|russell crowe|tom hanks|ellen degeneres golden globes|charlize theron golden globes|jennifer aniston golden globes|kate mckinnon golden globes|russell crowe golden globes|tom hanks golden globes
description: More Celebrity News ‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ http://bit.ly/SubClevverNewsThe Golden Globes had plenty of funny, shocking, and awkward moments. But what really got me were the emotional moments. I kid you not, I shed a couple tears tonight!What‚Äôs up? It‚Äôs Drew Dorsey here with Clevver News and award season is officially underway!There were so many moments to talk about, but I‚Äôm here to talk about the tear jerking moments. And grab your tissues because emotions were running high!Let‚Äôs start with Tom Hanks who was honored with the Cecil B. DeMille award.It was a huge honor and just the montage before his acceptance speech was enough to get me emotional. But his speech set me over the edge.When he thanked his wife there wasn‚Äôt a dry eye in the audience or at home. You have to see it for yourself.I mean, my heart can‚Äôt take it! And neither could fans on Twitter.One person said quote, ‚ÄúHARD TO NOT CRY WHEN TOM HANKS CRIES.‚ÄùAnd another said quote, ‚ÄúI MEAN. WOW. #TomHanks is a worldwide treasure and we need to protect him at all costs. Also, excuse me while I wipe up the entire lake of tears I shed during his speech. @tomhanks‚ÄùBRB still crying over this entire moment.And if that wasn‚Äôt enough to make you shed a tear, let‚Äôs talk about Kate McKinnon presenting Ellen DeGeneres with the Carol Burnett Award.She opened up about how Ellen made her feel comfortable with her sexuality and how she‚Äôs paved the way for many people in the LGBTQ+ community in Hollywood.And fans are really connecting with this moment as well.One person tweeted saying quote, ‚ÄúI became super emotional watching Ellen DeGeneres--that people sought to dim her light is unacceptable. All I can say is, Equality is non-negotiable. And @RepHartzler --your discriminatory + hateful views on the LGBTQ+ community have no place in Congress.‚ÄùAnd another said quote, ‚ÄúIt was amazing, and so was Kate Mckinnon‚Äôs introduction. It was just what I needed today. The world needs more Ellen‚Äôs.‚ÄùAnd we couldn‚Äôt agree more!The last emotional moment we will talk about for today, because I don‚Äôt want you all crying too much, is Jennifer Anniston talking about the Australian fires.Many celebs brought attention to the tragic fires that are currently happening in Australia.Jenn read Russell Crowe‚Äôs acceptance speech for him because he is back home in Australia helping his family affected by the fires.She got choked up when reading it and fans talked about this moment on Twitter.One fan tweeted saying quote, ‚ÄúNo, YOU were getting emotional watching Jennifer Aniston fighting off tears reading Russell Crowe's acceptance speech on the Australia fires.‚ÄùAnd another said quote, ‚ÄúJennifer Aniston did a superb job hosting and reading out Russel Crowe‚Äôs message with sincerity and empathy‚ÄùAnd we totally get it. The fires are tragic and we‚Äôd like to help however we can.In our description we‚Äôve linked some ways to donate and get involved. Please consider donating if you are able to!And I want to hear from you all which moment made you cry the most.Was it Tom Hanks or Kate McKinnon or someone else?Let me know down in the comments below.After that, why don‚Äôt you dive in to more Clevver News by hitting that subscribe button and click that bell so you don‚Äôt miss any of our new stories. Then click right over here for more Golden Globes coverage. Thanks for hanging out with me here on Clevver, I‚Äôm your host Drew Dorsey and I‚Äôll see you next time. description: The leader of Australia's eastern New South Wales state has declared a week-long state of emergency in response to the escalating bushfire threat.High temperatures and strong winds are forecast for the weekend, leading to widespread extreme fire danger.Troops are also preparing to evacuate some of the 4,000 people trapped by fires in neighbouring Victoria state.Since September, bushfires have killed 18 people and destroyed more than 1,200 homes across NSW and Victoria.At least 17 people remain missing after fires this week alone.Please subscribe HERE http://bit.ly/1rbfUog

title: Dani is leaving the band.
tags: cimorelli|cimorelli sisters|the cimorellis|dani cimorelli|cimorelli break up|dani cimorelli solo|dani leaving cimorelli|dani is leaving|cimorelli sisters split up|cimorelli band ending|cimorelli fighting|cimorelli fight|emmyn calleiro|dani and emmyn
description: Dear Cim Fam,It is with heavy hearts that we have to announce that Dani is leaving Cimorelli. She had the courage to share with us that she wants to pursue other career paths outside of YouTube and has made the decision to move on from the band. Of course, none of us wanted her to leave but we will always support her and love her no matter where life takes her. We wish her well with all her ventures and we hope you guys will too. This has been a very difficult decision for all of us to process and we know it‚Äôll be tough for you guys too but please be kind as we all move forward. We really appreciate your kindness during this time.The door will always be open for her if she ever wants to return. We love her as a sister first, and we always will. We remain very close to her as her family.We are grateful for the 10 years that we had with her in the band and we wish her the best in her new chapter of life.Rest assured that Cimorelli will continue in 2020 onward with the other 5 of us. 2019 was one of the best years ever for Cimorelli and we are so grateful we had Dani as a part of it. We will do our best to move forward and kick butt in our new format and we look forward to sharing many new projects with you all in 2020. We will be grieving right alongside all of you but will also do our best to uplift you guys along the way with our new projects.Love you guys and thank you for understanding.- Cimorelli

title: Google and Amazon are now in the oil business
tags: Vox.com|vox|explain|explainer|climate change|big oil|fracking|google|amazon|microsoft|artificial intelligence|machine learning|adam cole|global warming|big tech
description: Google, Microsoft, and Amazon are teaming up with Big Oil to squeeze more oil and gas out of the ground using machine learning technology.Subscribe to our channel! http://goo.gl/0bsAjOSources:Brian Merchant (Gizmodo) https://gizmodo.com/how-google-microsoft-and-big-tech-are-automating-the-1832790799Christopher M. Matthews (Wall Street Journal) https://www.wsj.com/articles/silicon-valley-courts-a-wary-oil-patch-1532424600Matt Novak (Gizmodo) https://paleofuture.gizmodo.com/article-from-1975-the-world-will-be-out-of-oil-by-2015-1732903871Kasia TokarskaDaniel CivitareseGhassan AlRegib - https://ghassanalregib.info/Google, Microsoft, and Amazon have been very vocal about their efforts to reduce the world's dependence on fossil fuels. But as The Wall Street Journal and Gizmodo have reported, these same companies are currently teaming up with fossil fuel industry to help them squeeze as much oil and gas out of the ground as possible. Oil has always been hard to find and hard to extract, and so the industry has teetered precariously on the edge of profitability several times over the course of its history. Over and over again, experts have predicted that we'll soon run out of accessible, affordable oil - but so far, they've been wrong. title: I filled my mountain bike brakes with baby oil for a year and here are the results!
tags: mtb|mountain bike|bike repair|biking|bike riding|bike tricks|bike trials|cycling|DIY|home improvement|outdoors|building
description: A little over a year ago we filled the rear hydraulic brake of my fat tire mountain bike with baby oil, instead of Shimano Brake oil. Now over a year later, we're going to tear apart the brakes and look at all the most vulnerable components under a microscope to see if they degraded or changed in any way.This video is just for entertainment, and I can't recommend that you fill your brakes with baby oil. With that said, this will always be the baby oil fat bike and it will always have baby oil in the brakes until they fail. Maybe it's time we name this bike... title: WHAT A PERFORMANCE! | HIGHLIGHTS | Arsenal 2-0 Manchester United | Jan 1, 2020
tags: Arsenal|Arsenal FC|Arsenal Football Club|Football|Club|EPL|Premier League|Soccer|Sport|Team|aubameyang|lacazette|bernd leno|torreira|guendouzi|ozil|bellerin|Kieran Tierney|Reiss Nelson|joe Willock|granit xhaka|rob holding|calum chambers|gabriel martinelli|bukayo saka|nicolas pepe|arsenal manchester united|arsenal man utd|pepe goal man uted|sokratis|david luiz|pepe goals|premier league highlights
description: We have our first win of the Mikel Arteta era thanks to a determined, energetic performance on New Year's Day. Nicolas Pepe fired us ahead with a first-time finish after Sead Kolasinac and Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang had cut Manchester United open down our left. Kolasinac made a storming run from left-back and stayed onside to receive a return pass from our captain before cutting the ball back for Pepe to finish. Pepe, now full of confidence, tricked his way into the box to set up Aubameyang for a volley over the bar, and Alex Lacazette miscued a shot after turning past Harry Maguire. You sensed we needed a second goal - especially after how Sunday's game against Chelsea panned out - and it arrived just before half-time. Pepe was the provider with an excellent corner delivery, Lacazette's flicked header was pushed out by David de Gea, and Sokratis was on hand to volley into the roof of the net. We were rather more circumspect after the break, happy to play on the break while United probed for a goal that would bring them back into the game. But they never got it, thanks largely to a gutsy rearguard action that was epitomised by the tigerish Lucas Torreira in front of defence. Three points, and a corner turned. This was the perfect start to 2020.#arsenal #nicolaspepe #mikelartetaFor more match action, highlights and training videos, make sure you become a digital member and sign up to Arsenal Player. This channel will look behind the scenes and get closer to the likes of Mesut Ozil, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang, Henrikh Mkhitaryan, Alexandre Lacazette, Bernd Leno, Granit Xhaka, Hector Bellerin, and more.ABOUT ARSENAL FCArsenal Football Club were formed in 1886. They have amassed 13 League titles, 13 FA Cups and many other major trophies since then. description: SUBSCRIBE for Every Theory! ‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ http://bit.ly/1qV8fd6The end of 2019 not only marks a time to look back on the top games of this year, but the top games that defined the entire decade of the 2010s.
